##How are those little city places you like? | sandwiches

WECHAT china30s

Feature description, a platform that encourages you to write about your life. Founded in March 2011, it has a sandwich writing school and a media platform, China Sandwich, at the same time, we are committed to applying the story to cross-border product design, urban culture excavation, exhibition fair, space creation and other three-dimensional field.

Few sights are as bleak as Shanghai, where the bare branches of the Platanus × Hispanica in winter spread out the streets as they once were. Roadside shops are mostly locked doors, occasionally glimpsed two or three pedestrians, we will deliberately maintain a distance, forward quickly.
There seems to be a quiet shuffle going on in the city. Under the pressure of rent, salary, passenger flow and so on, small stores have to make emergency adjustments to make themselves more adaptive to survive. But when the epidemic began to subside, and people's lives gradually returned to normal, can everything really be as it was?

This time we talked to five small shops in Shanghai that have story newsletters, ranging from cafes, bars, theme bookstores and grocery stores. In addition to being concerned about what decisions people have made about their stores in the recent past, i also wanted to know how they felt about the butterfly effect that came with this chaotic storm.

Interview, Essay | butter

Cafe noche

Type: Bar + CAFE / Shop Age: Koya 7 years, Koya 1 year two employees each

Tintin's two stores, "Koya" and "Koya" , are both located in the ancient North district, where the Japanese are concentrated. During the day, Koya is a japanese-style coffee shop. At night, it turns into the Zephyr Bar. Most of its regulars are Japanese. But in the import supermarket's small night is different, mainly serves in the take-away guest. Because of the outbreak, Tintin temporarily decided to suspend the small night of the day coffee plate operation, but for the sake of the bar's old guests, continue the tradition of non-closure on the night of the Spring Festival.

Narrator: Tintin

"Let's have a Nice Cup of coffee when things calm down. "

In the Spring Festival of 2019, I was in a car accident while riding a battery powered car. I accidentally twisted my ankle and had to cancel the coffee part of Xiaoye during the day. So if this year's Spring Festival does not sell coffee during the day, it is similar to last year's situation. I read online that February 2 to 9 is the outbreak period, in the cafeteria food cross-infection probability is still high, so did not open shop. After the 10th, if the numbers keep going up, we're GONNA have to limit the number of people we can get into the store, like nine people in 18 seats, rather than make less money and keep everyone safe.
But at night, it's a little tricky. The Bar's regular guests all know that we do not rest during the Spring Festival, this is already the seventh year. So with that in mind, cafe nightcap opens to the public at 20:00 PM -- 01:00. In previous years, there were quite a lot of people in the New Year. After the second day of the Lunar New Year, there were fewer people. Because most of the old guests are Japanese, New Year's Eve around the return ticket is more expensive, to 7,8,000, but a few days later to go, 5,000 can be done.
These days, there are only about three or four customers a night, which is just right. People still used to sit at the bar, and we tried to get two spaces between them. This year all the Japanese guests, one part is to stay in Shanghai for the New Year, the other part is the seventh day back to Shanghai but found that work delayed, and then fly back is not very convenient, can only work at home.
The Japanese guest's own protection measure does quite well, pays attention to disinfects, the clean, usually has wears the mask the custom. They said they saw people on the street wearing masks, but many wore them upside down and told me to pinch the metal to fit their noses better. Generally speaking, their panic is not as serious as ours. They feel that if they take good precautions, they will have no big problems, even joking from time to time, "Now that Mancheng District is covered with face masks, it doesn't feel like Shanghai, it's Tokyo in March and April with Hay fever. "
Another shop "small night" because in the city supermarket, and itself is positioned as take-out coffee shop, the risk of infection is relatively low. It's open for business, too. I'm just going back and forth from 2:00 in the morning to 2:00 in the afternoon at little night, and from night to night at little night. A little girl will come to Saya at noon to take my place. The rest of the staff had gone home for the holidays, and under the circumstances, they couldn't find anyone at the last minute, so that's it.

I still take breaks when I have time. I like coffee myself, but when I drink it in my own store, I stay in the mood for work, and it's not very relaxing. So on the afternoon of the New Year's Day, I went to OPS and ICHIKI's (two cafes in Shanghai) and had two cups of coffee.
Plans to start roasting coffee beans in stores in April have been slowed down. During the break in the day, I thought about my craft, and how the two stores I was running could make a difference.
Looking forward to the smooth after a good cup of coffee, I do not know if this is not a bit unenterprising.

Whalebone
Type: Bookstore / Store Age: 2 Years / 3 employees

In the summer of 2019, Jingzi bookstore moved from the residential lane of Zhonglu in Chongqing, Shanghai, to the bustling Xintiandi Business District, which became an "Internet celebrity punch-in" for a time and even required customers to enter the bookstore. When the epidemic broke out, the offline physical industry would be the first to be directly affected, but Zhang Ye, the manager of the complex bookstore whale brand, said they were ready to fight hard for three months.

DICTATION: Zhang Ye

"Times change all the time. It may not change slowly, it may change all at once. "

We're much better off than the offline focused stores, and we can take the loss if we close in February. That's because online illustration and visual arts courses account for about 80 percent of annual revenue, or 90 percent, before moving to the current location.
Last year, the whale has become the so-called "red shop" , single-line income, there is some profit, but not as much as everyone thought. The bookstore has always seemed to be an adjunct to the whale's overall business, and I wouldn't put it in the position of an attacker.
Although the store is not open until March 3, I will go to the store first this month to do some cleaning, cleaning, as well as a record of this rare period. We have a shop assistant in Wuhan, do not know how long will be locked up, and a small partner in Hebei, her train has stopped, and recently to see how to drive to Beijing and then back to Shanghai. The show, originally planned for early March, has been moved to mid to late March, and is less about attracting crowds and more about planning derivative sales.
Originally, the store's plan this year was also to put more effort into developing its own cultural and creative products, and to upgrade and optimize the process system, the theme display and the product structure again. These were mainly adjustments made after studying the customers'preferences, not entirely for flat sales, but also want to be able to increase the unit price. After all, there is a limit to the number of people that brick and mortar stores can accommodate.
In fact, many years ago it was difficult for bookstores to sell only books, and it would be unhealthy for them to operate on state subsidies. People needed to think about new business models to make ends meet. Many people think that online shopping is a big competitor to brick and mortar bookstores, but since you're aware of this, why not put online into the overall structure? Try not to put all your eggs in one basket. The above discussion may be limited to bookstores, not all industries need online business, but generally the same.
I read an article earlier that attributed the future of bookstores to a few patterns, and I thought it was pretty illuminating. One model is the membership bookstore, which packages the store's overall services, including different events, offers, lists, and so on, and then charges the community a membership fee to foster consumer habits and awareness. There is a model, like the whale, is a composite type, both its own thematic selection of books, there are small exhibitions, literary works, etc. , the overall framework is relatively rich state.
Speaking of SARS that year is the rise of Taobao, that period of time we all avoid going out not to store, the situation and now very similar. This outbreak if a lot of people's habits changed, the market for a new product model, it is more difficult for the traditional industry of small shops. This era is changing all the time. It may not change slowly, but it may change all at once.
My biggest fear is not knowing what the streets will look like after March. If everyone is afraid to go out easily, after work also avoid with friends party, shopping, you used to go to the store is gone, want to do things can not do, everything has to start again... Think is pretty scary.

Moon Coffee
Type: CAFE / Shop Age: 512 Years / 6 employees

With the increase in the number of confirmed cases, many communities in Shanghai have begun to block the doors, as the old moon coffee shop opened in Anfu road residential buildings, it can only be closed temporarily. However, long before news of the outbreak came out, Xiao Feng, the manager of the moon cafe, had stocked up all the milk for the two moon cafe stores during the Spring Festival.

Narrator: Xiaofeng

"This is probably the only time we've had a chance to talk through a mask, and we don't want that to happen again. "

The moon cafe is always open 24 / 7. In previous years, many guests in Shanghai did not want to visit relatives and friends, do not want to go too busy places, will come over with friends to drink coffee quietly. My friends and I are all from Shanghai, so we can take care of them for a few hours every day.
Now the whole city is deserted, the fourth day of the Fourth Street some shops have opened, but in February 10 as far as possible after the business notice has been closed. Our shop on Anfo road, it's in a neighborhood. Not long ago, we found that the community began to restrict access to people, every day closed the door, so also had to close the shop according to the community arrangements.
Our other shop is on South Maoming Road. It's a corner shop. These days are mainly some of the old guests, we are really too long at home, can not help but go out for a walk. Some friends come out can not stop, can not stop talking for an hour. This is probably the only time we've had a chance to talk through a mask, and I don't want that to happen again.
When news of the outbreak first came out, we had already arranged for two stores to stock up on goods during the Spring Festival. We were worried that there would not be enough. By my estimate, there will be about 30 bottles of wasted milk in the store this year. It really hurts. So we always ask our customers if they want to take a bottle of milk.
Speaking of which, both of our cafes are located in prime locations in Shanghai, and even if the outbreak occurs, the fixed costs can not be reduced, so we have to make temporary internal adjustments and make some remedial measures to deal with it.
In fact, many people have a daily demand for coffee, but due to the epidemic dare not go out, so this year's Spring Festival everyone on the demand for coffee beans increased. In the past, the coffee shop did a good job. We mainly took care of the customers in the shop. We didn't have much time to bake beans. Recently, we had to bake beans every other day. This year in this regard the benefit is really better than before, but because of express reasons, in fact, can only be provided to Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Shanghai area guests. Income, to make up some of it, but not much. Sometimes I think it's a good thing we bake at home, it's cheaper, and we have a chance to catch our breath, otherwise we really won't be able to sleep this Spring Festival.
However, these pressures have also forced me to think deeply about how to make the moon coffee more adaptable in its current environment. We didn't put a lot of effort into our online operations, and we kept thinking about how we could better serve our customers in the store. But after this incident, I think, perhaps we should pay more attention to the online, when such an incident again in the future, can have a chance to survive.

Gaman Cafe, my slow Cafe
Type: CAFE / Shop Age: 3 Years / Full Time 2 employees, part time 5 employees

When I slow opened, it was Yuyuan Road that built the road. After a year of trying to calm down, it was shut down because of the epidemic. Life seems to have hit the pause button in a split second, but the rent and payroll bills don't stop there. Not long ago, Molly wrote in a group of friends, "the coffee shop only has enough water to last a month. ".

Narrator: Molly

"I see so many people wanting to open cafes,
But in the end, I was stuck with this thing."

I've been through Atypical pneumonia, and I'm still scared to think about it. At that time, I had already transferred to Sichuan for more than half a year. My father also came to see me long before the incubation period of the epidemic, but the teachers and classmates still wanted to "arrest" us because we were Cantonese, eventually the family got away with all kinds of proof. Now, as a person living in Shanghai, I can understand their initial feelings of tension in the face of unknown viruses, but the trauma will never be able to heal.
There have been other stores open recently, but I decided, out of concern, not to open until February 10th. Don't take any chances, especially if your staff and customers might get infected. In addition, the shop has the small partner to take the train to come, also wants to be at home self-isolation for a period of time. From the information received so far, we do not have fever, onset, but there are fat conditions.
I sent out a message on my facebook page saying, "there's only enough water in the cafe for a month, " and it's true. Coffee shops live on water, I sent staff to training years ago, the machine is also re-repair, maintenance, then spent a lot of money. But people have to find a way, and I can't say that since I can only support a month, then shut it down. This store is like my baby, and my employees need me to pay them on time. I'm not the only one running a store anymore.
Most of my days in the business seemed to be spent on borrowing money. In 2018, our shop in Yuyuan Road road construction for a whole year, very affect passenger flow, that year is also very sad. I thought I was a very strong person, but in the second half of the road repair, or could not help but in the shop in front of the staff in the face of crying, from the bottom of my heart pretty desperate.
I've seen too many people try to open a coffee shop, and then they end up stuck with this thing. Some time ago I had a very low day, just chat with some fellow friends, we each say their own shop, feel much better after speaking out, is the mutual comfort between friends. I feel less pressure than some stores that need to stock up on fresh produce or hold up staff during the Spring Festival.
These days do not have to open a shop, I brush at home, cooking, but can not use a very relaxed state of mind to enjoy this "extra vacation" , life stuck here, stagnant, the bill did not stop.
Perhaps it will be better in the middle of summer, spring is a period of high incidence of disease. I've thought about it, and I'm going to put it out there as a 'save the children, ' so you're all welcome to come in for a cup of coffee. I also hope that my suppliers will be able to survive, we are in the same boat together. Although I do know that after March, there will be some losses.

OPEN THE MARKET
Type: GROCERY STORE AGE: 1 YEAR2 partner

Captain Flowers and Kya are THE founders of OPEN THE MARKET, a boutique, and THE only two employees in THE store. Their shop is located diagonally across the street from the Shanghai Library. On the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, the development of the epidemic is so alarming that many shops have chosen to postpone their opening. But captain flowers and Kya have not changed their original plans and are still going back to work. On the first day of business, he even photographed a Vlog, a self deprecating record of the empty streets outside the store.

Narrator: Captain Broken Flower
Narrator: Kya

"When you find that there's very little you can do right away,
It calms you down a lot."

We still in accordance with the original plan of the fifth day back to work opened the door, is holding a playful attitude, anyway at home also idle. The first week back to work, the daily reception is only 4 or 5 guests, most of them are foreigners. They receive less information and are less defensive than we are.
In such period, the problem that a lot of shops face is same, the weight that bears is different just. We are both in Shanghai and have no other staff. Most of the shops are selling cultural, clothing and so on, there is no short shelf life of the problem. The biggest cost to bear is rent. We all have to get back on track eventually, so it's not necessarily a bad thing for us to keep our shops open, but it might have a positive impact on people passing by.
However, these days to store business is false, two people want to meet, mutual discussion shop arrangement is true. We have been studying everyone's consumer needs, from the store to now, the store's product mix has been adjusted. When the outbreak is over, the customer's mentality, habits will be more or less some change, these two days we will be in the store to simulate the consumer's mentality may be what, in such an emergency situation we should stock.
Of course, many things will be put on hold, such as new plans for the new season that will come in the spring. We've done a survey before and found that our guests still have high expectations of our own original design, so now we're considering whether to devote all our time to it.
In the online part of the business, we don't want to just sell what we have online, but we want to do something interesting online, not just sell it. People stay home for so long, they're gonNA want to go out. It's a phase. Besides, it takes the same amount of effort to do this online as it does to run offline stores, and when you point that way, the appeal of offline stores is bound to be discounted.
Take, for example, why the cinema business has become so good in the past two years. When DVD came out in 2000, a lot of people were following it, but people still have to socialize with people, AH, offline shops still have their value, depending on how far you can go, how much more than online sales alone can offer.
We are a choice store, store this more than a year, we have been wondering whether to choose their own like or we will like? And it turns out, it's the former all the time. Only if you believe in it will you feel confident enough to recommend it to the people who trust you, which is probably why the store exists. We didn't do much social networking in the past, only interacting with people through wechat groups, but after this incident, we wanted to have more online expression of our attitudes and opinions.

The show, originally planned for early March, has been moved to mid to late March, and is less about attracting crowds and more about planning derivative sales.

Originally, the store's plan this year was also to put more effort into developing its own cultural and creative products, and to upgrade and optimize the process system, the theme display and the product structure again. These were mainly adjustments made after studying the customers'preferences, not entirely for flat sales, but also want to be able to increase the unit price. After all, there is a limit to the number of people that brick and mortar stores can accommodate.

In fact, many years ago it was difficult for bookstores to sell only books, and it would be unhealthy for them to operate on state subsidies. People needed to think about new business models to make ends meet. Many people think that online shopping is a big competitor to brick and mortar bookstores, but since you're aware of this, why not put online into the overall structure? Try not to put all your eggs in one basket. The above discussion may be limited to bookstores, not all industries need online business, but generally the same.

I read an article earlier that attributed the future of bookstores to a few patterns, and I thought it was pretty illuminating. One model is the membership bookstore, which packages the store's overall services, including different events, offers, lists, and so on, and then charges the community a membership fee to foster consumer habits and awareness. There is a model, like the whale, is a composite type, both its own thematic selection of books, there are small exhibitions, literary works, etc. , the overall framework is relatively rich state.

Speaking of SARS that year is the rise of Taobao, that period of time we all avoid going out not to store, the situation and now very similar. This outbreak if a lot of people's habits changed, the market for a new product model, it is more difficult for the traditional industry of small shops. This era is changing all the time. It may not change slowly, but it may change all at once.

My biggest fear is not knowing what the streets will look like after March. If everyone is afraid to go out easily, after work also avoid with friends party, shopping, you used to go to the store is gone, want to do things can not do, everything has to start again... Think is pretty scary.

Moon Coffee

Type: CAFE / Shop Age: 512 Years / 6 employees

With the increase in the number of confirmed cases, many communities in Shanghai have begun to block the doors, as the old moon coffee shop opened in Anfu road residential buildings, it can only be closed temporarily. However, long before news of the outbreak came out, Xiao Feng, the manager of the moon cafe, had stocked up all the milk for the two moon cafe stores during the Spring Festival.

Narrator: Xiaofeng

"This is probably the only time we've had a chance to talk through a mask, and we don't want that to happen again. "

The moon cafe is always open 24 / 7. In previous years, many guests in Shanghai did not want to visit relatives and friends, do not want to go too busy places, will come over with friends to drink coffee quietly. My friends and I are all from Shanghai, so we can take care of them for a few hours every day.
Now the whole city is deserted, the fourth day of the Fourth Street some shops have opened, but in February 10 as far as possible after the business notice has been closed. Our shop on Anfo road, it's in a neighborhood. Not long ago, we found that the community began to restrict access to people, every day closed the door, so also had to close the shop according to the community arrangements.
Our other shop is on South Maoming Road. It's a corner shop. These days are mainly some of the old guests, we are really too long at home, can not help but go out for a walk. Some friends come out can not stop, can not stop talking for an hour. This is probably the only time we've had a chance to talk through a mask, and I don't want that to happen again.
When news of the outbreak first came out, we had already arranged for two stores to stock up on goods during the Spring Festival. We were worried that there would not be enough. By my estimate, there will be about 30 bottles of wasted milk in the store this year. It really hurts. So we always ask our customers if they want to take a bottle of milk.
Speaking of which, both of our cafes are located in prime locations in Shanghai, and even if the outbreak occurs, the fixed costs can not be reduced, so we have to make temporary internal adjustments and make some remedial measures to deal with it.
In fact, many people have a daily demand for coffee, but due to the epidemic dare not go out, so this year's Spring Festival everyone on the demand for coffee beans increased. In the past, the coffee shop did a good job. We mainly took care of the customers in the shop. We didn't have much time to bake beans. Recently, we had to bake beans every other day. This year in this regard the benefit is really better than before, but because of express reasons, in fact, can only be provided to Jiangsu, Zhejiang and Shanghai area guests. Income, to make up some of it, but not much. Sometimes I think it's a good thing we bake at home, it's cheaper, and we have a chance to catch our breath, otherwise we really won't be able to sleep this Spring Festival.
However, these pressures have also forced me to think deeply about how to make the moon coffee more adaptable in its current environment. We didn't put a lot of effort into our online operations, and we kept thinking about how we could better serve our customers in the store. But after this incident, I think, perhaps we should pay more attention to the online, when such an incident again in the future, can have a chance to survive.

Gaman Cafe, my slow Cafe

Type: CAFE / Shop Age: 3 Years / Full Time 2 employees, part time 5 employees

When I slow opened, it was Yuyuan Road that built the road. After a year of trying to calm down, it was shut down because of the epidemic. Life seems to have hit the pause button in a split second, but the rent and payroll bills don't stop there. Not long ago, Molly wrote in a group of friends, "the coffee shop only has enough water to last a month. ".

Narrator: Molly

"I see so many people wanting to open cafes,
But in the end, I was stuck with this thing."

"I see so many people wanting to open cafes,

But in the end, I was stuck with this thing."

I've been through Atypical pneumonia, and I'm still scared to think about it. At that time, I had already transferred to Sichuan for more than half a year. My father also came to see me long before the incubation period of the epidemic, but the teachers and classmates still wanted to "arrest" us because we were Cantonese, eventually the family got away with all kinds of proof. Now, as a person living in Shanghai, I can understand their initial feelings of tension in the face of unknown viruses, but the trauma will never be able to heal.
There have been other stores open recently, but I decided, out of concern, not to open until February 10th. Don't take any chances, especially if your staff and customers might get infected. In addition, the shop has the small partner to take the train to come, also wants to be at home self-isolation for a period of time. From the information received so far, we do not have fever, onset, but there are fat conditions.
I sent out a message on my facebook page saying, "there's only enough water in the cafe for a month, " and it's true. Coffee shops live on water, I sent staff to training years ago, the machine is also re-repair, maintenance, then spent a lot of money. But people have to find a way, and I can't say that since I can only support a month, then shut it down. This store is like my baby, and my employees need me to pay them on time. I'm not the only one running a store anymore.
Most of my days in the business seemed to be spent on borrowing money. In 2018, our shop in Yuyuan Road road construction for a whole year, very affect passenger flow, that year is also very sad. I thought I was a very strong person, but in the second half of the road repair, or could not help but in the shop in front of the staff in the face of crying, from the bottom of my heart pretty desperate.
I've seen too many people try to open a coffee shop, and then they end up stuck with this thing. Some time ago I had a very low day, just chat with some fellow friends, we each say their own shop, feel much better after speaking out, is the mutual comfort between friends. I feel less pressure than some stores that need to stock up on fresh produce or hold up staff during the Spring Festival.
These days do not have to open a shop, I brush at home, cooking, but can not use a very relaxed state of mind to enjoy this "extra vacation" , life stuck here, stagnant, the bill did not stop.
Perhaps it will be better in the middle of summer, spring is a period of high incidence of disease. I've thought about it, and I'm going to put it out there as a 'save the children, ' so you're all welcome to come in for a cup of coffee. I also hope that my suppliers will be able to survive, we are in the same boat together. Although I do know that after March, there will be some losses.

OPEN THE MARKET

Type: GROCERY STORE AGE: 1 YEAR2 partner

Captain Flowers and Kya are THE founders of OPEN THE MARKET, a boutique, and THE only two employees in THE store. Their shop is located diagonally across the street from the Shanghai Library. On the fifth day of the Lunar New Year, the development of the epidemic is so alarming that many shops have chosen to postpone their opening. But captain flowers and Kya have not changed their original plans and are still going back to work. On the first day of business, he even photographed a Vlog, a self deprecating record of the empty streets outside the store.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Narrator: Captain Broken Flower

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Narrator: Kya

"When you find that there's very little you can do right away,
It calms you down a lot."

"When you find that there's very little you can do right away,

It calms you down a lot."

We still in accordance with the original plan of the fifth day back to work opened the door, is holding a playful attitude, anyway at home also idle. The first week back to work, the daily reception is only 4 or 5 guests, most of them are foreigners. They receive less information and are less defensive than we are.
In such period, the problem that a lot of shops face is same, the weight that bears is different just. We are both in Shanghai and have no other staff. Most of the shops are selling cultural, clothing and so on, there is no short shelf life of the problem. The biggest cost to bear is rent. We all have to get back on track eventually, so it's not necessarily a bad thing for us to keep our shops open, but it might have a positive impact on people passing by.
However, these days to store business is false, two people want to meet, mutual discussion shop arrangement is true. We have been studying everyone's consumer needs, from the store to now, the store's product mix has been adjusted. When the outbreak is over, the customer's mentality, habits will be more or less some change, these two days we will be in the store to simulate the consumer's mentality may be what, in such an emergency situation we should stock.
Of course, many things will be put on hold, such as new plans for the new season that will come in the spring. We've done a survey before and found that our guests still have high expectations of our own original design, so now we're considering whether to devote all our time to it.
In the online part of the business, we don't want to just sell what we have online, but we want to do something interesting online, not just sell it. People stay home for so long, they're gonNA want to go out. It's a phase. Besides, it takes the same amount of effort to do this online as it does to run offline stores, and when you point that way, the appeal of offline stores is bound to be discounted.
Take, for example, why the cinema business has become so good in the past two years. When DVD came out in 2000, a lot of people were following it, but people still have to socialize with people, AH, offline shops still have their value, depending on how far you can go, how much more than online sales alone can offer.
We are a choice store, store this more than a year, we have been wondering whether to choose their own like or we will like? And it turns out, it's the former all the time. Only if you believe in it will you feel confident enough to recommend it to the people who trust you, which is probably why the store exists. We didn't do much social networking in the past, only interacting with people through wechat groups, but after this incident, we wanted to have more online expression of our attitudes and opinions.
